Pre-Game Insights: England manager Gareth Southgate decided not to risk captain Harry Kane due to a back injury.

Jude Bellingham, Kobbie Mainoo, Phil Foden, and Kyle Walker were set to join the team later due to recent club commitments.
Bukayo Saka was rested ahead of Friday's tie with Iceland.
Ollie Watkins was expected to lead the line with Cole Palmer and Eberechi Eze as supporting cast.
Trent Alexander-Arnold was tested in a midfield slot again.
Marc Guehi and Lewis Dunk were expected to benefit in the backline.
